            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Funding for NASA's Science Mission Directorate to ensure the U.S. maintains global leadership in space exploration and scientific discovery.\n* Supports high-tech manufacturing in NJ-05 with local contractors including Spectro Analytical Instruments, KDF Technologies, and Kulite Semiconductor Products.\n* Sustains the specialized aerospace workforce and STEM pipeline required to compete with China's rapidly expanding lunar and planetary science programs.\n* Drives a 3:1 economic return on investment while advancing peer-reviewed Decadal Survey priorities for Earth science, planetary defense, and astrophysics.",
            "rationale": "Uses provided advocacy talking points on U.S. leadership and competition with China. Incorporates local NJ-05 spending data by citing specific contract recipients (Spectro Analytical, KDF Technologies, Kulite) from the provided context.",
