            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "This request seeks $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) to restore stability and maintain U.S. leadership in space exploration. Following recent funding volatility, this investment supports critical Decadal Survey priorities and ensures the U.S. remains the global leader in the face of rising international competition, particularly from China. This funding directly impacts New Jersey's 5th District, supporting high-tech manufacturing and research at local firms like Spectro Analytical Instruments, Inc. and KDF Technologies LLC, which have contributed to NASA missions through over $314,000 in recent agency obligations. NASA Science delivers outsized returns in discovery, national prestige, and practical applications that drive our domestic innovation economy.",
            "rationale": "Combines the specific $9B request with local economic impact data (Spectro Analytical Instruments, KDF Technologies) and strategic talking points regarding international competition and workforce stability.",
